Per-arg span resolution must build SpanPathIndex once and resolve every positional arg through it; the stale and list/show resolvers each reimplement this loop and must never reintroduce a per-arg corpus-reload helper (spans_matching_path_in / matching_span_names_in), which turns a shell-expanded glob of hundreds of args against a large span set into an O(args x spans) freeze. The compiler accepts either form, so this contract is unenforced.
